word_mean_info__list.difference: 多指浸没，侧重最后结果。
普通用词，一般指水所发挥的作用。
指吸进或覆盖着一点水份，常表示潮湿得使人不舒服。
指微湿，侧重不干，但并非湿得使人不快。
普通用词，指各种潮湿的状态。

list.abstract: 《Wet》是美国歌手Nicole Scherzinger演唱的歌曲。收录在Nicole Scherzinger2011年3月发行的专辑《killer love》中。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't play in the wet grass, George.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能在潮湿的草丛里玩，乔治。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't play in the wet grass, George. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能在潮湿的草丛里玩，乔治。噢。

yingyinNormal.en: Teddy! I left Teddy in the garden! He'll get wet!
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰迪！我把泰迪忘在花园里了！他会淋湿的！

yingyinNormal.en: George is going to play in the wet grass. Oh, dear. Peppa loves playing in the wet grass, but she doesn't want to get her new shoes wet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治在潮湿的草丛里玩。噢糟糕，佩琪也喜欢在潮湿的草丛里玩，但她不想把新鞋子弄湿。

yingyinNormal.en: George is going to play in the wet grass. Oh, dear. Peppa loves playing in the wet grass, but she doesn't want to get her new shoes wet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治在潮湿的草丛里玩。噢糟糕，佩奇也喜欢在潮湿的草丛里玩，但她不想把新鞋子弄湿。

yingyinNormal.en: After all, the spread of bacteria is more likely to occur with wet skin and rubbing your wet hands on your clothes or touching the bathroom door can often contaminate them even more.
yingyinNormal.zh: 毕竟，在湿皮肤上，细菌容易传播手湿湿的擦在衣服上，或者去握厕所把手，只会使手更脏。

yingyinNormal.en: Crime wave in Gotham. Other breaking news: "Water, wet." Did you file the football yet?
yingyinNormal.zh: 哥谭市暗流涌动，另一条爆炸新闻是“水是湿的”，你写好橄榄球赛的稿子了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Teddy. I left Teddy in the garden. He'll get wet. Don't worry, Peppa. Daddy Pig will rescue Teddy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰迪，我忘了把泰迪带回来，他会被淋湿的。别担心，佩琪。爸爸这就去救泰迪。

yingyinNormal.en: Poor Daddy Pig. He must have been cold and wet. And now where is he? What's that sound? It sounds like snoring!
yingyinNormal.zh: 可怜的猪爸爸，他现在一定又冷又是湿的。他去什么地方了？这是什么声音？好像是打鼾的声音！

yingyinNormal.en: You look cheerful! And wet!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看起来挺高兴！还湿透了！

yingyinNormal.en: Right. And that's not wet cement.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，这也不是湿水泥。

yingyinNormal.en: You smell of wet grass and biscuits.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你问起来有股湿草地和饼干的味道。

yingyinNormal.en: George is going to play in the wet grass.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治将要去湿草坪上玩耍。

yingyinNormal.en: Elia wouldn't let the wet nurse touch them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伊莉亚都不让乳母碰他们。

yingyinNormal.en: Listen, before I forget, that side is still wet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听着，趁着我还记得，那边油漆未干。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear. Peppa loves playing in the wet grass, but she doesn't want to get her new shoes wet. I can't play in the wet grass, George. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，天哪。佩佩喜欢在湿草坪上玩耍，但是她不想把她的新鞋弄湿。我不能在湿草坪上玩耍，乔治。噢。

yingyinNormal.en: What do I smell of? You smell of wet grass and biscuits.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我身上的气味呢？你问起来有股湿草地和饼干的味道。

yingyinNormal.en: It has been raining all night and now the garden is very wet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下了一整夜的雨，花园里很潮湿。

yingyinNormal.en: It has been raining all night and now the garden is very wet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一晚上都在下雨，现在花园里很湿。

word_usage.usage: wet作形容词时，可在句中作定语或表语。
wet用作名词指“雨天；湿地”时，通常用作单数形式，其前须加定冠词the。

wet用作动词时是及物动词，后接名词或代词作宾语，例：
Wet the brush slightly before putting it in the paint.
把刷子弄湿点再去沾油漆。
